  "description": "Oracle's maqam gravity parameter pulls Osprey's shore blend toward land — high gravity anchors the GENDY waveform tightly to a maqam scale, and simultaneously draws the coastline inward (more land, less open sea). When gravity releases and the waveform drifts free of the modal ladder, the shore opens: the coastal blend sweeps outward toward open water. The maqam and the shore are the same axis described in two vocabularies. Set oracle_gravity above 0.7 for a landlocked oracle; below 0.3 the prophecy drifts offshore and the coast dissolves into horizon.",
